  "prompt": "Does Quora censor questions?",
  "response": "Yes, Quora does have moderation policies in place that can lead to the censorship of certain questions and answers. The platform has guidelines to ensure that content is appropriate and does not violate their policies, which include prohibitions against hate speech, harassment, misinformation, and other harmful content. If a question is deemed to violate these guidelines, it may be removed or censored. Additionally, questions that are deemed irrelevant, overly promotional, or not conducive to productive discussion may also be moderated. This is part of Quora's effort to maintain a respectful and informative environment for users.",
